00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,680
We simply don't have enough human cycles

215
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:05,160
to prioritize cyber incidents.

216
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:08,160
We need to leverage the
superpower of the cloud,

217
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:10,699
and apply machine learning and AI

218
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:14,290
to implement artificial prioritization,

219
00:11:14,290 --> 00:11:18,699
AI to analyze incidents and
prioritize them for response.

220
00:11:18,700 --> 00:11:22,730
Extended detection and
response, or XDR solutions,

221
00:11:22,730 --> 00:11:26,400
that bring all the data from
the entire attack surface,

222
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:31,400
network, endpoint, cloud,
IoT, et cetera, into one place

223
00:11:31,510 --> 00:11:33,960
and leverage cloud-based analytics

224
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:37,133
is a recipe for artificial prioritization.

225
00:11:38,270 --> 00:11:40,949
By prioritizing based on risk

226
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:43,290
and protecting what matters most,

227
00:11:43,290 --> 00:11:47,372
we will ensure that when we
fall, we will withstand it.

228
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:51,160
The third aspect of resilience

229
00:11:51,160 --> 00:11:54,930
is rising up stronger
when we inevitably fall.

230
00:11:54,930 --> 00:11:56,030
So let's review a story

231
00:11:56,030 --> 00:11:58,930
about sewing machines to understand this.

