supports nearly 2
million low-income women,

234
00:12:04,170 --> 00:12:06,939
their families, and their
communities in India.

235
00:12:06,940 --> 00:12:09,790
The pandemic and India's lockdown

236
00:12:09,790 --> 00:12:11,983
have been particularly hard for SEWA.

237
00:12:13,250 --> 00:12:16,680
But after 49 years of helping
its members persevere,

238
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:20,150
SEWA knows the powerful
role a community plays

239
00:12:20,150 --> 00:12:22,709
in responding to a crisis.

240
00:12:22,710 --> 00:12:25,820
When the lockdown forced everyone indoors,

241
00:12:25,820 --> 00:12:28,930
women from across SEWA turned
to their sewing machines

242
00:12:28,930 --> 00:12:31,489
to make masks for government officials,

243
00:12:31,490 --> 00:12:34,180
hospitals, and their families.

244
00:12:34,180 --> 00:12:37,390
As India braves the second
wave of the pandemic,

245
00:12:37,390 --> 00:12:40,430
SEWA and other organizations
around the world

246
00:12:40,430 --> 00:12:44,260
continue to play a critical
role in provisioning oxygen,

247
00:12:44,260 --> 00:12:47,490
plasma, money, and other supplies.

248
00:12:47,490 --> 00:12:48,820
If you have the means,

249
00:12:48,820 --> 00:12:52,450
I ask that you consider
supporting their efforts.

250
00:12:52,450 --> 00:12:56,820
The SEWA story shows that those
that belong to a community

251
00:12:56,820 --> 00:12:59,993
rise up stronger because
they rise up together.

